INTP General Survey Analysis 2017

This was written for the Being an INTP Facebook Page by Anne Dorko.

If you know your MBTI Personality type, you can contribute to the dataset by completing the survey. New survey submissions are regularly cleaned and fed through this analysis for the highest quality results. All numbers and reports below are based on the latest cleaned data.

General Information

This data is primarily for fun, and cannot be considered scientific. That said, I have done my best to make the data as quantifiable as possible. This exercise has been more for the practice of data cleaning and analysis, and I like to share my work.

91% of the respondents were INTP, which is not represenative of the general popualation. Because of this, the otherwise general results are heavily weighted towards any INTP tendencies. Notes have been made through this page to let you know when INTPs have been completely isolated to run INTP-specific analysis.

You can also see that more females than males took this survey. We do not have enough data to determine whether this means INTPs are more likely to be women, as our sample is a convenience sample and not a true random sample.

It is also important to note that the majority of test takers were assigned their MBTI type through an online test or assigned it to themselves after reading through all 16 profiles. This means that our sample may or may not be ‘true’ INTPs (if such a thing exists). However, as this is only in good fun, for the sake of this study we will assume that the MBTI personality types are accurate.

The Parents of an INTP

In the survey, respondents are asked to give information about their parents. In total, MBTI personality types were provided for 210 individuals that are parents to INTP respondents. This accounts for 1.8 parents reported per INTP.

Female Parent Figures

As you can see below, female parents of INTPs tend to be ISFJ, ISTJ, INFJ, and ESFJ. It appears that very few INTPs have mothers who are also INTPs!

Male Parent Figures

Contrary to female parent figures, more fathers of INTPs also tend to be INTPs themselves, followed in frequency by ISTJ and ISTP. This is particularly interesting as, in general, female INTPs signficantly outweigh male INTPs throughout the rest of the data.

MBTI Personalities and Romance

Going in, it is again important to note that the highest amounts of information we have are for INTPs. What we are looking for is patterns in frequent pairings. Due to the imbalance of data for INTPs, one cannot assume that these patterns apply evenly for other types of MBTI personality types.
